Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read the Prime Minister’s address for the latest information.

Belize has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Belize, see Return to the UK
Travel restrictions and borders
With effect from 23 March, the Government of Belize closed all borders including suspending all international flights to the Philip Goldson International Airport (Belize City). These restrictions will be reviewed as part of state of emergency review. Exit out of Belize during this time will not be possible.
Local Measures
The government of Belize has announced a nationwide state of emergency for the country. This went into effect at midnight on Wednesday 1 April and includes a curfew from 8.00pm to 5.00am every day. The state of emergency is to last for 30 days in the first instance. For its duration, people are advised to stay at home even during daylight hours and only to come out if absolutely necessary for shopping and doing essential business only. Supermarkets, grocery stores, banks and credit unions will open for agreed times.
Exercise may be taken between 05.00 – 08.00 daily (except Sunday). Cargo and essential imports will continue to come into the country. Visit the Government of Belize Press Office Facebook page to stay up to date.
The Belize authorities will be strictly enforcing the state of emergency, physical distancing, self-isolation, quarantining and other such rules. Anyone who violates these may be liable for fines and imprisonment for up to one year.
Visas
The Belize authorities has suspended visitor visa extensions or permits until further notice. This measure has been taken to observe the restrictions of the state of emergency. Once the state of emergency is lifted, all outstanding immigration fees will need to be paid.
Medical Care
If you are showing COVID-19 symptoms – fever, shortness of breath, coughing or difficulty breathing – call 0800 MOH CARE / 0800 664 2273.
The British High Commission in Belmopan remains open and operational but staff are working remotely to comply with local Ministry of Health guidelines. We are committed to supporting British Nationals in Belize for the necessary consular services during this time.
If you need urgent assistance, call +501 822 2146. The British High Commission, Belmopan is issuing regular updates on Facebook with the latest available information.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
